SIMPLE: misconceive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misconceive
<hw>Mis`con*ceive"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Misconceived</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Misconceiving</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To conceive wrongly; to
interpret incorrectly; to receive a false notion of; to misunderstand;
to misjudge; to misapprehend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those things which, for want of due consideration heretofore, they
have <qex>misconceived</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To misapprehend; misunderstand;
mistake.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misconceiver</ent>⟦br⟧
